WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:07.200 --> 00:00:11.730
If you have just arrived to Dublin,
it is time to visit NED Training Centre

00:00:11.730 --> 00:00:14.200
and check any questions you have with your agent.

00:00:14.800 --> 00:00:18.200
This video shows your first steps in Ireland.

00:00:18.400 --> 00:00:21.000
Your agent will alleviate all your doubts.

00:00:21.600 --> 00:00:25.800
During the conversation, you will receive
a letter to get your PPS Number.

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:28.000
Inform your agent of your local address

00:00:28.100 --> 00:00:32.000
and within 5 days, you will receive a Bank Letter at your house.

00:00:32.100 --> 00:00:35.500
This one cannot be opened. We will talk about that later.

00:00:35.800 --> 00:00:41.800
After the conversation, your agent will lead you
to take the Placement Test to determinate your English level.

00:00:41.900 --> 00:00:45.200
You will receive your Placement Test result by email.

00:00:45.500 --> 00:00:47.900
The next step will be getting your PPS Number.

00:00:48.200 --> 00:00:53.500
It is very easy, free and the PPS building
is really near NED Training Centre.

00:00:53.600 --> 00:01:00.000
To get your PPS number, remember to take your Passport
and your PPS Letter provided by your agent.

00:01:00.100 --> 00:01:03.900
PPS is your identification number for the Irish Government.

00:01:04.100 --> 00:01:07.400
Once you have your PPS, it is time to open a bank account.

00:01:07.600 --> 00:01:10.300
Do you remember that letter that we told you not to open?

00:01:10.300 --> 00:01:15.900
You must take that letter, your enrolment letter
and your Passport to open a bank account.

00:01:16.100 --> 00:01:21.600
In between 5 and 10 days, you will receive your PIN code and bank card by mail.

00:01:21.700 --> 00:01:26.700
Remember to make the deposit only after you have received your PIN code and bank card.

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:31.000
After 24 hours, go to the bank and request an account statement,

00:01:31.200 --> 00:01:34.000
which you shall receive within five working days.

00:01:34.100 --> 00:01:36.800
This document is needed for get your GNIB card.

00:01:37.000 --> 00:01:45.500
Having received the bank statement, go to the GNIB office with your Passport, enrolment Letter, Bank Statement and PPS number.

00:01:45.700 --> 00:01:48.000
Your agent will advise of the best way to pay.

00:01:48.200 --> 00:01:51.800
E.U. students do not need to get a GNIB card.

00:01:51.800 --> 00:01:56.700
And that is it! Now, all you have to do is
ticking everything Ireland has to offer!

00:01:57.000 --> 00:01:58.100
Enjoy your experience!

00:01:58.400 --> 00:02:06.200
NED Training Centre. Here, you invest in your future!

